[DJW:] In both these cases, you can enter them directly as they 
are in the default character encoding (at least for Amaya 
3.1 on NT). [DJW:] --------------------------- DISCLAIMER --------------------------------- Any views expressed in this message are those of the individual sender, except where the sender specifically states them to be the views of BTS. 
The entity &amp;nbsp; can be inserted in Amaya by Control+space. 
When saving a document Amaya generates the ISO-Latin 1 code of the character 
instead of the entity value. 
We could change the Amaya export if you think that the entity is better. 
Irene. 
Please use numeric (e.g., &amp;#160;) rather than named entities to maintain closer compatibility with XML. 
